Fans in attendance at the Miloud Hadefi Stadium in Oran were treated to a highly entertaining evening of African football after Mali and Angola played out to a high-scoring 3-3 draw in the opening Group D match of the TotalEnergies African Nations Championship (CHAN).           Cameroon tactician Alioum Saidou on the other hand is happy with his side's 1-0 win over Congo in their first Group E match. The last time the two sides met at the CHAN was in 2018 in Morocco with the Red Devils edging Cameroon 1-0 thanks to a goal by Junior Makiesse. Congo head coach Jean Elie Ngoya Obackas has admitted that his side could have won against neighbours and arch-rivals Cameroon if only they had an ounce of self-belief